get.description: Gets the status of a single export job.

exportId.description: The ID of the export to get.

create.description:
Creates a new Export Job for the user.  This will return immediately,
the ID in the response can then be used to poll GetExport to tell when
the job is done.

exportId.description: The ID of the export to cancel.

key.description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

quotaUser.description: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters.

fields.description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

enumDescriptions: v1 error format
v2 error format

oauth_token.description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

enumDescriptions: Responses with Content-Type of application/json
Media download with context-dependent Content-Type
Responses with Content-Type of application/x-protobuf

location.description:
Location of the error, as specified by the location type.

If location_type is PATH, this should be a path to a field that's
relative to the request, using FieldPath notation
(net/proto2/util/public/field_path.h).

Examples:
  authenticated_user.gaia_id
  resource.address[2].country

debugInfo.description:
Debugging information, which should not be
shared externally.

code.description:
Error code in the error domain. This should correspond to
a value of the enum type whose name is in domain. See
the core error domain in error_domain.proto.

enumDescriptions:
location is an xpath-like path pointing
to the request field that caused the error.

other location type which can safely be shared
externally.

Location is request paramater. This maps to the {@link PARAMETERS} in
{@link MessageLocation}.

argument.description:
Error arguments, to be used when building user-friendly error messages
given the error domain and code.  Different error codes require different
arguments.

externalErrorMessage.description:
A short explanation for the error, which can be shared outside Google.

Please set domain, code and arguments whenever possible instead of this
error message so that external APIs can build safe error messages
themselves.

External messages built in a RoSy interface will most likely refer to
information and concepts that are not available externally and should not
be exposed. It is safer if external APIs can understand the errors and
decide what the error message should look like.

domain.description:
Error domain. RoSy services can define their own
domain and error codes. This should normally be
the name of an enum type, such as: gdata.CoreErrorDomain

Errors.description:
Request Error information.

The presence of an error field signals that the operation
has failed.

code.description:
Global error code. Deprecated and ignored.
Set custom error codes in ErrorProto.domain and ErrorProto.code
instead.

requestId.description:
Request identifier generated by the service, which can be
used to identify the error in the logs

failedItemInfos.description:
The set of items that couldn't be included in the archive.
If a directory was specified in ExportRequest.items and items in that
directory failed, each individual file that failed will have an entry in
failed_item_infos.

enumDescriptions:
The export is in an unknown state, this value should never be set
if received it may indicate you client doesn't have the latest set
of enum values.

The export has been submitted but an archiver hasn't started working
on it yet.

An archiver is working on this export, it is currently enumerating
all the resources so we know how much work there is to do.
The export is currently in the process of being built.

The export is finished and completed successfully.  This will be
the result even if some individual files failed. failed_items will
be populated with id of any items that failed to be included in the
archive.

The export is finished and failed.  This represents a catastrophic
failure in the infrastructure and not a failure to fetch individual
items. failed_items will not be populated in this case.
debug_failure_info will contain more info about the failure.
status.description: The current status of this export job.

debugFailureInfo.description:
Detailed information about what failed in the case status = FAILED.
This information is for internal debugging only and should not be shared
with user.

archives.description:
A set of records that contain information about the completed archives
created by this job.  This will only be present if status = SUCCEEDED.

items.description:
The items being exported. If a directory is present all
items under that directory will be included.

id.description: The ID of this job. Can be used to get or cancel this job.

ExportJob.description:
The representation of an export job.  Used for creating new jobs
and reporting the state of existing jobs.

locale.description:
Allows the client to specify a locale for the request.
The format of the string is an IETF
language tag, such as "en-US", as defined in
BCP 47 (http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). More practically, the content
of the string should be one that is appropriate for creating a java
Locale object.  Defaults to "en-US" if not specified.

items.description:
The requested items to export. If a directory is specified, all
items under that directory will be exported, but only top-level
items are captured in this field.

enumDescriptions: Used for Dasher Russia and China Flume jobs
Used for legal removal of social data / long term retention exports
Used to differentiate scheduled jobs that come from the UI
DTP Jobs
Used by takeout for troubleshooting

archivePrefix.description:
Optional prefix for the archive filename. Will be followed by a '-'
& an ISO standard timestamp in yyyyMMdd'T'HHmmssZ format. Prefix
defaults to "takeout" if none specified, resulting in an archive
name like "takeout-20150924T221439Z.zip".

ExportRequest.description: A request to create a new export.

CreateExportResponse.description: The result of a request to create a new export.

errors.description: If present provides details on any errors that occurred.

FailedItemInfo.description: Info about a failed item (file or folder) in an export.

title.description:
The user visible title of the item that failed, empty if the failure was
due to permissions.

enumDescriptions: The default value for the enum, isn't expected in production.
A failure that we weren't able to assign a specific cause to.
The specified ID was not found.
This item was marked as prevent colaborators from downloading.
This item failed the virus check.
cause.description: The cause of the failure, if known.

relativePath.description:
The path to the failed item from one of the root items specified when
starting the export.  The path includes the file name.
If this item is reachable via multiple paths (e.g. the individual item
was selected as well as the parent folder or the item is multi-included
in several folders) it is undefined (and non-deterministic) which root
node this path will be relative to.

docId.description: The document ID of the item that failed.

mediaType.description: The mime type of the file.

Archive.description: A completed archive file (e.g. zip or tgz).

storagePath.description: The downloadable url of the completed archive.

compressedSize.description: The size, in bytes, of the compressed archive.

fileName.description:
The full name of the archive file, including extension (but not
including path).

sizeOfContents.description: The size, in bytes, of all the items in the archive.

percentDone.description:
Percent done (# completed files) / (# total files).
Included for BUILDING exports only.

numFetchedFiles.description:
Total number of fetched files. Set for completed exports only.
If a folder containing 2 files was downloaded, num_fetched_files = 2.

errors.description: If present provides details on any errors that occurred.

TakeoutItem.description: Represents an item (file/folder/album) in the product.

id.description:
The ID of the item, must line up with the id that that service's
Takeout integration produces.

CancelExportResponse.description: The result of a request to cancel a given export.

errors.description: If present provides details on any errors that occurred.

succeeded.description: Whether the export was successfully cancelled
